---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Aruba Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/aruba/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Curacao for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/curacao' },
  { title: 'Netherlands for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/netherlands' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'arubaFit', header: 'Aruba Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AWG$880-1,255/mo', arubaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AWG$1,030-1,470/mo', arubaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AWG$790-1,130/mo', arubaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'AWG$735-1,050/mo', arubaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AZV (Local)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: 'AWG$200-400/mo', arubaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'AWG$790-1,255', annual: 'AWG$9,480-15,060' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'AWG$1,085-1,675', annual: 'AWG$13,020-20,100' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'AWG$1,460-2,250', annual: 'AWG$17,520-27,000' },
  { category: 'AZV Public Insurance', monthly: 'AWG$200-400/mo', annual: '~2% of income' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'AWG$1,500-3,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Aruba 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Aruba. Dutch territory, happy island vibes, beautiful beaches, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Aruba"
  subheadline="Aruba offers 'One Happy Island' lifestyle, Dutch governance, beautiful beaches, and year-round sunshine—a Caribbean retirement destination with good healthcare for island standards."
  heroImage="/images/countries/aruba-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Aruba</h2>
  <p>
    Aruba offers reliable sunshine, beautiful beaches, Dutch-Caribbean culture, and safe environment. Outside the hurricane belt, Aruba has minimal storm risk. For those seeking Caribbean retirement with stability, Aruba delivers though at moderate-high costs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Oranjestad is the capital with shops and services. Palm Beach/Eagle Beach areas offer resort living. Noord and Paradera have residential communities. San Nicolas in the south is more local. The entire island is compact (70 sq miles) and easy to navigate.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good for Caribbean; Dr. Horacio Oduber Hospital</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dutch, Papiamento, English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> AWG$5,000-10,000/month (~$2,800-5,600 USD); moderate-high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical desert; sunny; outside hurricane belt</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Safe; happy; multicultural</li>
      <li><strong>Dutch Connection:</strong> Part of Kingdom of Netherlands</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Aruba Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Aruba has good healthcare for its size—Dr. Horacio Oduber Hospital is the main facility. Most routine care handled locally. Complex cases require travel to Colombia, Miami, or Netherlands. AZV is the mandatory health insurance system for residents.
  </p>

  <p>
    AZV covers all residents with income-based premiums (~2%). Additional private coverage recommended for international options. Netherlands is backup for complex care (long flight). Colombia provides closer alternative for some procedures.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">AZV System</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Aruba has mandatory AZV health insurance—covers all residents. Premiums are income-based (~2%). Covers local care and some overseas treatment. Additional international insurance recommended for seniors wanting US/Europe options.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Aruba offers residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Retired Person Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with guaranteed income. Demonstrate financial independence. Application through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in Aruba business. Various investment thresholds.
  </p>

  <h3>Dutch Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Kingdom of Netherlands citizenship allows settlement. Administrative registration required.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities receive 30-90 days visa-free. Extensions possible. Some use extended visits.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Aruba:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residents:</strong> AZV mandatory for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Retiree permits:</strong> May require private insurance proof</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental:</strong> Recommended for international coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Include US/Netherlands coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Aruba</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      AZV provides local base coverage for residents. International insurance supplements with US/Europe access for complex conditions. Colombia hospitals offer nearby alternative. Dutch connection provides European healthcare access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Aruba, AZV plus supplemental recommended:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Aruba</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AZV:</strong> Mandatory local system; good base coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Americas + worldwide coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Dutch options:</strong> Some coverage extends from Netherlands</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare supplemental coverage for Aruba.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Aruba (AWG pegged ~1.79 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AZV reliance:</strong> Mandatory coverage is comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce supplemental premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Colombia option:</strong> Nearby quality care alternative</li>
    <li><strong>Dutch connection:</strong> Netherlands healthcare for complex needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Dutch Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €3,000/month pension. Dutch citizenship. Palm Beach area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> AZV mandatory + European Health Insurance Card for NL visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> AZV ~AWG$300/month. Kingdom connection; dual healthcare access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,500/month pension. Retiree permit. Oranjestad.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> AZV + Cigna Global for US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> AZV + ~AWG$1,000/month supplement. Local care; US backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Venezuelan Expatriate, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month income. Investor permit. Noord area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> AZV + Allianz Care for Colombia/US options.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> AZV + ~AWG$850/month. Close to South America; multiple options.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Aruba really outside hurricane belt?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—location in southern Caribbean means hurricanes rarely affect Aruba. Last significant hurricane was 1877. Trade winds bring steady breeze but no major storms. Climate advantage over most Caribbean islands.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Dutch?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No—English widely spoken in Aruba. Papiamento is local creole language. Dutch is official but not essential for daily life. Most Arubans speak 4+ languages. English speakers navigate easily.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How is Aruba healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Good for Caribbean standards—Dr. Horacio Oduber Hospital handles most needs. Specialists available. Complex cases may require travel (Colombia, Miami, Netherlands). AZV covers referrals when needed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Aruba safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of safest Caribbean destinations. Low violent crime. Petty theft exists in tourist areas. Safe to walk around. Generally welcoming environment for retirees.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Aruba coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Aruba authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
